javadoc:
Settings objects store name-value pairs.  Each SettingsDefinition defines one
 or more names to use to store values in settings objects.  Exactly what type
 of value and how to interpret the value is done by the SettingsDefinition object.

params.comment: the key used to retrieve a value

params.name: name

params.name: name

return.comment: the byte[] value for a key

methods.name: getValue
methods.comment: Gets the object associated with the given name

params.name: name
params.comment: the key used to retrieve a value

methods.name: setLong

params.name: value

methods.name: setString

params.name: value
params.comment: the value associated with the key

methods.name: setByteArray

params.name: value
params.comment: the value associated with the key

methods.name: setValue
